* '''1947 (Shōwa 22)''': Flooding from the {{ill|Typhoon Kathleen|ja|カスリーン台風|qq=draft}} caused extensive damage, with 300+ fatalities, 40,000 flooded homes, and 25,000 ha of inundated farmland in Tochigi Prefecture. * '''1986 (Shōwa 61)''': Typhoon 10 caused significant flooding, inundating 46 ha and 200+ houses. * '''1997 (Heisei 9)''': Typhoon 7 led to 35 ha of flood damage. * '''1998 (Heisei 10)''': Heavy rain caused 81 ha of flood damage. * '''2019 (Reiwa 1)''': {{ill|Typhoon Hagibis|ja|令和元年東日本台風|qq=draft}} caused widespread flooding. Water levels exceeded the danger threshold for 9 hours, and significant inundation occurred in western Utsunomiya.<ref name="bousai">{{Cite web|url=https://www.zenkokubousai.or.jp/monthly/image/no857high.pdf|author=Tochigi Prefecture River Section|title=Reiwa Year 1 Disaster in Tochigi Prefecture|publisher=National Disaster Association|access-date=2022-09-19}}</ref>
