== Geography == The Tagawa originates in the low mountains of Shichiri in Nikkō and the watershed of {{ill|Shidobuchi River|ja|志度淵川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shidobuchi River|qq=}}. It passes through areas like Nikkō's Inokura, Utsunomiya's Ishinata and Tokujirō towns, and Utsunomiya City Center, eventually flowing through Kawada, Yokota, [[:en:Kaminokawa, Tochigi|Kaminokawa]] Ishida, [[:en:Shimotsuke, Tochigi|Shimotsuke]] Yachiga, and [[:en:Oyama, Tochigi|Oyama]] Enjimashinden before joining the Kinugawa River via the diversion channel.
The river's total length is 78 km, and its basin area covers 245.8 km², making it the largest tributary of the Kinugawa River. Tagawa's tributaries include 11 first-class rivers such as {{ill|Akaborigawa|ja|赤堀川 (栃木県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akaborigawa|qq=}} and {{ill|Yamadagawa|ja|山田川 (栃木県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamadagawa|qq=}}.
